5. Observations & Recommendations
Code Quality: The 
MoonPhase.js
 component works well but is quite large (>300 lines). It mixes physics logic, animation loops, and UI rendering.
Refactoring Opportunity: Extract the physics calculations (orbital positions) into a custom hook (e.g., useOrbitalPhysics) to clean up the component.
React 19: The project is using the latest React 19, which is excellent.
Performance: The animation uses requestAnimationFrame, which is the correct approach for smooth simulations.
Next Steps: The 
EscapeVelocity
 module is explicitly marked as "future work" in the code comments. This is a prime candidate for the next development task.
6. How to Run
Install dependencies: npm install
Start local server: npm start
Build for production: npm run build